1 Data import

wavegram <- read_csv("../results/wavegram.csv") %>%
    separate(file, c("speaker", "phonation")) %>%
    mutate(
        phonation = ordered(phonation, levels = c("modal", "breathy")),
        speaker_phon = ordered(interaction(speaker, phonation))
    ) %>%
    mutate_if(is.character, as.factor) %>%
    filter(sequence < 8)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   file = col_character(),
##   token = col_integer(),
##   time = col_double(),
##   sequence = col_integer(),
##   sample = col_double(),
##   amplitude = col_double()
## )

2 Analysis

2.1 S01

s01_gam <- bam(
    amplitude ~
        phonation +
        s(sequence, k = 8) + s(sample) +
        s(sequence, by = phonation, k = 8) + s(sample, by = phonation) +
        ti(sequence, sample, k = 8) +
        ti(sequence, sample, by = phonation, k = 8),
    data = filter(wavegram, speaker == "01")
)

summary(s01_gam)
## 
## Family: gaussian 
## Link function: identity 
## 
## Formula:
## amplitude ~ phonation + s(sequence, k = 8) + s(sample) + s(sequence, 
##     by = phonation, k = 8) + s(sample, by = phonation) + ti(sequence, 
##     sample, k = 8) + ti(sequence, sample, by = phonation, k = 8)
##

    s01_gam,
    view = c("sequence", "sample"), 
    comp = list(phonation = c("modal", "breathy")),
    zlim = c(-1, 1)
)

)

2.3 All speakers

phonation_gam <- bam(
    amplitude ~
        phonation +
        s(sequence, k = 8) +
        s(sample) +
        s(sequence, by = phonation, k = 8) +
        s(sample, by = phonation) +
        ti(sequence, sample, k = 8) +
        ti(sequence, sample, by = phonation, k = 8) +
        s(sequence, speaker_phon, bs = "fs", m = 1, k = 8),
    data = wavegram,
    method = "ML"
)

summary(phonation_gam)
## 
## Family: gaussian 
## Link function: identity 
## 
## Formula:
## amplitude ~ phonation + s(sequence, k = 8) + s(sample) + s(sequence, 
##     by = phonation, k = 8) + s(sample, by = phonation) + ti(sequence, 
##     sample, k = 8) + ti(sequence, sample, by = phonation, k = 8) + 
##     s(sequence, speaker_phon, bs = "fs", m = 1, k = 8)
## 
## Parametric coefficients:

## (Intercept)       0.31604    0.02154  14.674   <2e-16 ***
## phonationbreathy  0.07008    0.03046   2.301   0.0214 *  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Approximate significance of smooth terms:
##                                         edf Ref.df         F p-value

)

##     k = 8) + s(sequence, speaker_phon, bs = "fs", m = 1, k = 8)
